    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Published_GetDegreeDayInformation",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve degree day information for a specified billing period. Degree days are a measure used to estimate energy consumption based on temperature variations. The procedure fetches data from a user-defined function "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Factors.uftn_GetDegreeDayInformationForReporting",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and returns various metrics related to cooling and heating degree days for both the current and prior fiscal years. The procedure also adjusts the billing period based on user type."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity of this stored procedure is considered medium. It involves conditional logic based on user type, dynamic parameter assignment, and interaction with a user-defined function. The procedure is straightforward in terms of SQL operations but requires understanding of business rules and data structures."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@PublishedBillingPeriod AS VARCHAR(6)",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": This parameter specifies the billing period for which the degree day information is to be retrieved. It is expected to be in a format that can be interpreted as a billing period identifier."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@IsAgencyUser AS BIT = 0",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": This is a flag indicating whether the user is an agency user. If set to 1, the procedure will dynamically set the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@PublishedBillingPeriod",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " to the current processing period from the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Billing.ApplicationTimeFrame",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " table."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "4. Business Logic and Workflow"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "orderedList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Transaction Isolation Level",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure sets the transaction isolation level to "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "READ UNCOMMITTED",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", allowing it to read uncommitted changes from other transactions. This is typically used to avoid locking issues and improve performance at the risk of reading dirty data."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Agency User Check",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": If the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@IsAgencyUser",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " parameter is set to 1, the procedure updates the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@PublishedBillingPeriod",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " to the current processing period by querying the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Billing.ApplicationTimeFrame",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " table where "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "CurrentProcessingPeriod",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " is 'Y'."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Data Retrieval",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure calls the function "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Factors.uftn_GetDegreeDayInformationForReporting",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " with the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@PublishedBillingPeriod",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " parameter to retrieve degree day information. The function returns a dataset with various metrics related to cooling and heating degree days for both the current and prior fiscal years."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Output",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure selects and returns the data retrieved from the function, which includes descriptions, fiscal year data, degree day metrics, and delta changes in degree days."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
